2026-07-24 10:00:00", "open": 4048.02849, "high": 4050.38681, "low": 4041.5471, "close": 4050.35203}, {"time": "2026-07-24 11:00:00", "open": 4050.18834, "high": 4050.46945, "low": 4040.89385, "close": 4042.11243}, {"time": "2026-07-24 12:00:00", "open": 4042.44289, "high": 4049.08487, "low": 4023.81048, "close": 4024.22131}, {"time": "2026-07-24 13:00:00", "open": 4024.89677, "high": 4033.02236, "low": 4022.1065, "close": 4028.91776}], "calendar": [], "editorial": "Gold is trading at $4,028 as the European afternoon session progresses on 24 July, consolidating in the lower half of yesterday's range after a sharp two-day reversal from the $4,165 area. The daily chart paints a picture of a market that has been unable to sustain its most recent push higher, with the broader structure now showing a sequence of lower highs since the $4,202 peak printed on 6 July.\n\nThe structure story over the past month has been one of contested territory. Gold surged from the $3,950 region in late June, rallying aggressively through early July to tag the $4,202 prior reaction zone \u2014 a level that has now attracted sellers on four separate occasions. That rejection was emphatic: the subsequent decline from $4,202 unwound nearly three weeks of gains within a handful of sessions, with the 22 July spike to $4,165 now looking like a failed retest of the breakdown zone rather than a resumption of the bull leg. The prior reaction zone around $3,957 remains the key structural support to the downside, having held on three prior tests. Between current price and that floor sits relatively thin structure, with the $4,000 psychological level the most obvious near-term reference point.\n\nThe hourly picture reinforces the bearish read. Price peaked at $4,141 in the early hours of 23 July and has since carved out a clean sequence of lower highs and lower lows across the H1 timeframe. The descent accelerated through the $4,090\u2013$4,095 congestion band during yesterday's afternoon, and overnight consolidation between $4,040 and $4,060 has resolved to the downside this morning. The most recent H1 candles are pressing toward the $4,022 session low, with momentum firmly in the sellers' favour at the intraday level.\n\nThere are no scheduled data releases or central bank events on today's calendar, which means the session is likely to be driven by positioning and technical flows rather than a fundamental catalyst. The absence of a news trigger cuts both ways \u2014 without a shock to reprice risk, the path of least resistance suggested by the chart may be allowed to play out more cleanly, but equally there is no obvious catalyst to accelerate a move toward the $3,957 support zone in a single session.\n\nThe bearish read would require reassessment if price were to reclaim and close above the $4,095\u2013$4,100 area on an hourly basis, as that would suggest the intraday downtrend structure has been broken. A daily close back above $4,165 would materially challenge the broader bearish framing and bring the $4,206 prior reaction zone back into focus as a potential magnet. Until such a reclaim occurs, the structure continues to favour the downside scenario.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}